Program: Free Thinking
Title: Kate Grenville
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b05wz4jk
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 3 Jun 2015
Kate Grenville is one of Australia's leading authors whose novels have explored her country's often difficult history. She and Rana Mitter discuss past secrets and present concerns as she publishes a memoir One Life: My Mother's Story. In her trilogy The Secret River, The Lieutenant, and Sarah Thornhill, Kate Grenville explored Australia's early history through three generations of a colonial family. Image: Kate Grenville Photo Credit: Darren James. Show less